rs--identifies the manner in which old problems (like the presumption that our object of study is a special, deeply meaningful case) yet remain in the field. But amidst the critique there are a variety of practical suggestions for how the science of religion can become methodologically even-handed and self-reflexive--the markings of a historically rigorous exercise--Provided by publisher.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="596"><subfield code="a">43</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Religion</subfield><subfield code="x">Methodology.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Religion</subfield><subfield code="x">Study and teaching.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="830"><subfield code="a">Supplements to Method &amp; theory in the study of religion ;</subfield><subfield code="v">v. 2.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="949"><subfield code="a">BL 41 M353 2015</subfield><subfield code="c">1</subfield><subfield code="h">UAHS-B</subfield><subfield code="i">0162035225950</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="926"><subfield code="a">BL 41 M353 2015</subfield><subfield code="w">LC</subfield><subfield code="c">1</subfield><subfield code="i">0162035225950</subfield><subfield code="d">1/13/2017</subfield><subfield code="e">1/13/2017</subfield><subfield code="k">CHECKEDOUT</subfield><subfield code="l">ON_SHELF</subfield><subfield code="m">UAHSS</subfield><subfield code="n">7</subfield><subfield code="p">$150.00</subfield><subfield code="r">M</subfield><subfield code="s">Y</subfield><subfield code="t">BOOK</subfield><subfield code="u">1/28/2015</subfield></datafield></record>